name: Carnival Carnivore
oracle_text:
Deathtouch
When Carnival Carnivore enters the battlefield, you get {TIX}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own.
flavor_text: Somehow only the third-most dangerous ride in the park.

name: Black Hole
oracle_text: Destroy target creature and up to X other target creatures, where X is the number of Attractions you've visited this turn.
flavor_text:
"Code Dark Donut! Code Dark Donut! All available fun specialists, please report to the Roil Coaster immediately!"
—Truss, chief engineer

name: Discourtesy Clerk
oracle_text:
When Discourtesy Clerk enters the battlefield, open an Attraction. (Put the top card of your Attraction deck onto the battlefield.)
At the beginning of your end step, if you control three or more Attractions, you draw a card and you lose 1 life.
flavor_text: Myra doesn't pay the vampires to smile—but only because guests found it off-putting.

name: Deadbeat Attendant
oracle_text: When Deadbeat Attendant enters the battlefield, open an Attraction. (Put the top card of your Attraction deck onto the battlefield.)
flavor_text: Some people will hire anyone with a pulse. Myra isn't that picky.

name: Haberthrasher
oracle_text:
Deathtouch
Whenever another creature that has a hat enters the battlefield under your control or a hat sticker is put on a creature you control, each opponent loses 1 life.
flavor_text: "Brims" Barone's enforcers are always dressed to kill.

name: Exit Through the Grift Shop
oracle_text: Yell "Who wants a souvenir?" and announce the name of a nonland card in your graveyard. Each player in an Un-game who can hear you may bid life. You start the bidding at 0. The high bidder loses life equal to the high bid. They copy the card and may cast the copy without paying its mana cost. If you didn't win the bid, you gain life equal to the high bid and create that many Treasure tokens.

name: Down for Repairs
oracle_text: Target opponent reveals their hand. You choose a nonland card from it. That player discards that card. Destroy up to one Attraction that player controls. (It's put into their junkyard.)
flavor_text: Safety twelfth.

name: Dissatisfied Customer
oracle_text:
Flying, haste
When Dissatisfied Customer enters the battlefield, roll a six-sided die. If the result is 3 or less, you lose that much life.
flavor_text: The mirrors weren't fun for everyone.

name: Disemvowel
oracle_text: Destroy target creature. That creature's controller loses 1 life for each unique vowel in the creature's name. (The vowels are A, E, I, O, U, and Y.)
flavor_text: Without vowels, no one can hear you scream.

name: Questionable Cuisine
oracle_text: Return up to two target creature cards from your graveyard to your hand. Create a Food token for each trash can you can see from your seat. (It's an artifact with "{2}, {T}, Sacrifice this artifact: You gain 3 life.")
flavor_text: May contain soy. May contain a deep void, chillingly hoarse and howling without voice. May contain gluten.

name: Photo Op
oracle_text:
Before the game begins, you may post a picture of yourself posing like the art of any Magic card with #GuessThatMagicCard and no other text.
You may reveal a reply posted today with a guess and a card you own from outside the game with the same name as that guess. Put that card into your hand. Exile Photo Op.

name: Night Shift of the Living Dead
oracle_text:
After you roll a die, you may pay 1 life. If you do, increase or decrease the result by 1. Do this only once each turn.
Whenever you roll a 6, create a 2/2 black Zombie Employee creature token.
flavor_text: At the Astrotorium, even the dead make a living wage.

name: Line Cutter
oracle_text: When Line Cutter enters the battlefield, roll to visit your Attractions.
flavor_text: Waiting is for chumps with flimsy spacesuits.

name: Last Voyage of the _____
oracle_text:
When this enchantment enters the battlefield, you may put a name sticker on it, then it becomes an Aura with enchant creature. Return a creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield and attach this Aura to it.
Enchanted creature gets +2/+0 for each name sticker on this Aura with seven or fewer letters.
When this Aura leaves the battlefield, sacrifice enchanted creature.

name: Scared Stiff
oracle_text: Scared Stiff has menace as long as you control a stickered permanent.
flavor_text: The horrors of Sorin's Haunted Mansion scared Hurrk half to life.

name: Rat in the Hat
oracle_text: {T}, Sacrifice Rat in the Hat: Until end of turn, you may cast target creature card that has a hate from your graveyard.
flavor_text: While the gremlin, beeble, and squirrel infestations wrecked havoc on the park, Roxi was able to spin the numerous rat colonies as a "robust recycling program."

name: Quick Fixer
oracle_text:
Menace
Whenever Quick Fixer deals combat damage to a player, open an Attraction. (Put the top card of your Attraction deck onto the battlefield.)
flavor_text: Myra doesn't believe in stopping rides for minor inconveniences like "they need to be repaired."

name: A Real Handful
oracle_text:
As long as one or more hands are touching A Real Handful, it gets +2/+2.
As long as two or more hands are touching A Real Handful, it has menace.
As long as three or more hands are touching A Real Handful, it has lifelink.

name: Xenosquirrels
oracle_text:
Xenosquirrels enters the battlefield with two +1/+1 counters on it.
After you roll a die, you may remove a +1/+1 from Xenosquirrels. If you do, increase or decrease the result by 1.
flavor_text:
"Hey Glaxxar, did you remember to seal the vents on the seat belt control module?"
—Truss, chief engineer

name: Wolf in _____ Clothing
oracle_text: When this creature enters the battlefield, you may put a name sticker on it. When you do, up to X target creatures each get -1/-1 until end of turn, where X is the number of unique vowels on that sticker. (The vowels are A, E, I, O, U, and Y.)
flavor_text: "And to think, I came in here looking for someone to eat."

name: Step Right Up
oracle_text: Open two Attractions. (Put the top two cards of your Attraction deck onto the battlefield.)
flavor_text:
"Ah, the midway, beating heart of the—well, maybe the big top is the heart. If there were two hearts then the midway—or the lungs. Lungs or stomach!"
—Captain Rex Nebula

name: Soul Swindler
oracle_text:
As long as you've visited an attraction this turn, Soul Swindler has indestructible. (Damage and effects that say "destroy" don't destroy it.)
When Soul Swindler enters the battlefield, open an Attraction. (Put the top card of your Attraction deck onto the battlefield.)
flavor_text: "Three tries to decide your fate! Fabulous prizes! Probably no untold torment!"

name: Six-Sided Die
oracle_text:
Choose target creature. Roll a six-sided die.
1 — It has base power and toughness 1 until end of turn.
2 — Put two -1/-1 counters on it.
3 — Six-Sided Die deals 3 damage to it and you gain 3 life.
4 — It gets -4/-4 until end of turn.
5 — Destroy it.
6 — Exile it.

name: Scooch
oracle_text:
Add or subtract 1 from target creature's power, target player's life total, or target die roll's result.
Draw a card.
flavor_text:
"What? No, that's ridiculous! Of course the rat doesn't work for the park. I've never seen it before in my life!"
—Monoxa, midway manager

name: _____ Balls of Fire
oracle_text:
When this enchantment enters the battlefield, you may put a name sticker on it.
Whenever you put a sticker on this enchantment, it deals damage equal to the number of o's in name stickers on this enchantment to any target.
flavor_text: Employees were instructed to refer to meteor showers as "impromptu fireworks."

name: Art Appreciation
oracle_text: Put an art sticker on a nonland permanent you own. Then ask a person outside the game to rate its new art on a scale from 1 to 5, where 5 is the best. When they rate the art, up to that many target creatures can't block this turn.
flavor_text: There's no defending against public opinion.

name: Amped Up
oracle_text:
This spell costs {1} less to cast for each electrical socket in a wall or floor you can see from your seat.
Gain control of target creature until end of turn. Untap that creature. Until end of turn, it gets +3/+0 and gains haste.
flavor_text: Space can be a lawless place—far from the praying eyes of electrical inspectors.

name: Aardwolf's Advantage
oracle_text: Creature you control get +2/+0 and gain alpha strike until end of turn. (A creature with alpha strike has first strike as long as it's blocking or being blocked by a creature that comes after it alphabetically.)
flavor_text:
"My Abattoir Ghoul deck is unbeatable. Wait, 1996 World Champion?"
—Johnny, to Spike

name: Don't Try This at Home
oracle_text:
If a hot source you control would deal damage, it deals that much damage plus 1 instead. (Something is hot if it has hot things in its art, like fire or explosions.)
{1}{R}, Sacrifice Don't Try This at Home: It deals damage equal to twice the number of hot cards in your graveyard to target creature or planeswalker.

name: Circuits Act
oracle_text: Roll three six-sided die. For each different result, create a 1/1 white Clown Robot artifact creature token.
flavor_text: Another day, another item Pietra has to add to the "do not juggle" database.

name: Carnival Barker
oracle_text: {T}: You have thirty seconds to laud a creature you control to any people outside the game. Until end of turn, that creature gains trample and haste and gets +X/+0, where X is the number of those people who appluaded. Activate only as a sorcery and only once.

name: Big Winner
oracle_text: Big Winner has trample as long as you control a stickered permanent.
flavor_text: The results of the test of strength were: Yes.

name: Ignacio of Myra's Marvels
oracle_text:
As Ignacio of Myra's Marvels enters the battlefield, choose armor, blood, book, bottle, fang, fire, scroll, spear, sword, or water.
Whenever you cast a spell with the chosen object in its art, create two Treasure tokens.
Partner (You can have two commanders if both have partner.)

name: Goblin Girder Gang
oracle_text:
Reach
Whenever you roll a result not stored on Goblin Girder Gang, you may store that result on it. When you do, Goblin Girder Gang deals 1 damage to any target without a hat.
Goblin Girder Gang gets +1/+0 for each result stored on it.

name: Goblin Cruciverbalist
oracle_text:
Haste
When Goblin Cruciverbalist enters the battlefield, create a colorless artifact token named your choice of A, E, I, O, or U.
Whenever Goblin Cruciverbalist attacks, using the first letters of names of permanents you control, spell a word you haven't spelled this game. It gets +1/+0 until end of turn for each letter in that word.

name: _____ Goblin
oracle_text: When this creature enters the battlefield, you may put a name sticker on it. Add {R} for each unique vowel on that sticker. (The vowels are A, E, I, O, U, and Y.)
flavor_text: The Astrotorium has never been a place for self-restraint.

name: Eelectrocute
oracle_text:
Eelectrocute deals 2 damage to any target.
You may cast Eelectrocute from your graveyard as long as you've rolled a 6 this turn. If you cast Eelectrocute this way and it would be put into your graveyard, exile it instead.
flavor_text: The midway's games aren't so much rigged as they are insulated and grounded.

name: Priority Boarding
oracle_text: Whenever you roll a die, you may reveal the top card of your library. Do this only once each turn. Whenever you reveal a card with mana value less than the result this way, you may exile it. If you do, you may play it this turn.
flavor_text: The Astrotorium's express lane is practically its own ride.

name: Opening Ceremony
oracle_text: Add {W}{U}{B}{R}{G}{C}. You may open a sealed Magic booster pack. Until end of turn, you may cast spells from among the cards in that booster pack.
flavor_text:
"Oooooh!"
—The crowd
"Aaaaaaaaah!"
—Also the crowd

name: One-Clown Band
oracle_text: {2}{R}: Target Robot gets +2/+0 until end of turn.
flavor_text: Programmed to play more than seventy instruments and only one song.

name: Non-Human Cannonball
oracle_text: When Non-Human Cannonball dies, roll a six-sided die. If the result is 4 or less, Non-Human Cannonball deals that much damage to you.
flavor_text: Designed for maximum impact, comedic and otherwise.

name: Minotaur de Force
oracle_text:
Haste
When Minotaur de Force enters the battlefield, you get {TIX}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own.
flavor_text: "If I ever need a haircut, I just fall a little to the left."

name: Wee Champion
oracle_text: Whenever you place a sticker, Wee Champion gets +1/+1 until end of turn. If it's an art sticker, instead put a +1/+1 counter on Wee Champion.
flavor_text: Nobody has ever won the bear, but then again, nobody has ever wanted it quite as much.

name: Trigger Happy
oracle_text: Choose a triggered ability of target permanent. It triggers. You control that ability.
flavor_text: Whenever you copy a triggered ability, you may do a little dance.

name: Ticking Mime Bomb
oracle_text: When Ticking Mime Bomb enters the battlefield, without speaking or indicating any specific creature, pantomime to a person outside the game, then they choose a creature you don't control. Ticking Mime Bomb deals damage equal to twice the number of Robots you control to the chosen creature.
flavor_text: Silent, but deadly.

name: Slight Malfunction
oracle_text:
Choose one —
• Destroy target artifact.
• Roll a six-side die. When you do, Slight Malfunction deals 1 damage to each of up to X target creatures, where X is the result.
flavor_text:
"Attention, valued patrons. The Tilt-o-Squirrel is now closed."
—Astrotorium public address system

name: Rad Rascal
oracle_text: When Rad Rascal enters the battlefield, open an Attraction. (Put the top card of your Attraction deck onto the battlefield.)
flavor_text: "Rent a scooter and be just like Devil K. Nevil! Just don't go faster than the speed limit. Or jump over anything. Or catch on fire. Or break every bone in your body multiple times. Other than that, just like him!"

name: Proficient Pyrodancer
oracle_text:
When Proficient Pyrodancer enters the battlefield, you may put an art sticker on a nonland permanent you own.
{2}{R}: Another target creature with an art sticker on it gets +2/+0 and gains menace until end of turn.
flavor_text: When she performed, she was on fire, but in a good way.

name: Well Done
oracle_text: Well Done deals 5 damage to target creature. If that creature is rare or mythic rare, Well Done deals 3 damage to that creature's controller.
flavor_text:
"What's the big deal? I've been on fire eighty-one times. Twice just while sleeping."
—Devil K. Nevil, daredevil extraordinaire

name: Chicken Troupe
oracle_text:
Ward {2} (Whenever this creature becomes the target of a spell or ability an opponent controls, counter it unless that player pays {2}.)
When Chicken Troupe enters the battlefield, you get {TIX}, then you may put a sticker on a nonland permanent you own.
flavor_text: Why did the chicken cross the park? To get to the other ride.
